Both files emitted. Schema validates: 25 iterations, 109 hypotheses, 106 analyses.

**Headline finding:** Only `treatment_palbociclib` shows a clinically meaningful PFS effect — adjusted +2.92 months in the subgroup defined by `er_positive=1 AND her2_positive=0 AND pik3ca_mutation=0` (n=18,681; p≈0). Outside this 3-feature cell the effect collapses to ≈0. The unfavorable values that nullify benefit are `her2_positive=1` and `pik3ca_mutation=1`; absence of `er_positive` also abolishes it. Within the responsive subgroup, higher `ki67_pct` attenuates the gain (-0.053 mo per %). All five other treatments (tamoxifen, trastuzumab, olaparib, sacituzumab govitecan, pembrolizumab) showed no robust subgroup effect after adjustment, including in their canonical biomarker-defined subgroups. Apparent crude signals (e.g., olaparib in BRCA1+, pembro in premenopausal TNBC) attenuated to near-zero once `age_years` (r=+0.70 with PFS, the dominant prognostic feature) was adjusted for.
